Called from `index.js` after both modules are loaded.

### New export: `notifyQuietHoursItem(filename)`

Fire-and-forget (does NOT await user input — no `pendingDecision` involvement). Sends a message to `CHANNEL_ID` with an Expedite button:

```js
async function notifyQuietHoursItem(filename) {
  if (!client) return;
  const displayName = filename.replace(/\.md$/, '').replace(/-/g, ' ');
  const row = new ActionRowBuilder().addComponents(
    new ButtonBuilder()
      .setCustomId(`research_expedite:${filename}`)
      .setLabel('▶️ Run now')
      .setStyle(ButtonStyle.Primary),
  );
  await channel.send({
    content: `📥 **Research queued** (quiet hours active): *${displayName}*\nClick to run immediately.`,
    components: [row],
  }).catch(err => logger.warn(`discord-bot: notifyQuietHoursItem failed (${err.message})`));
}
```

### `interactionCreate` — add expedite branch

```js
if (interaction.customId.startsWith('research_expedite:')) {
  const filename = interaction.customId.slice('research_expedite:'.length);
  await interaction.deferUpdate();
  if (expediteHandler) {
    await expediteHandler(filename);
    await interaction.editReply({ content: `▶️ Expediting *${filename.replace(/\.md$/, '')}*…`, components: [] });
  } else {
    await interaction.editReply({ content: '⚠️ Expedite handler not registered.', components: [] });
  }
}
```

### `messageCreate` — `!research` commands

Add inside `init()`, after the existing `interactionCreate` handler:

```js
client.on('messageCreate', async (message) => {
  if (message.author.bot) return;
  if (message.channelId !== CHANNEL_ID) return;
  const text = message.content.trim().toLowerCase();
  if      (text === '!research hold')    await handleHoldCommand(message, true);
  else if (text === '!research release') await handleHoldCommand(message, false);
  else if (text === '!research status')  await handleStatusCommand(message);
});
```

`handleHoldCommand(message, activate)`:
- Calls `researchGate.setHold(activate)`
- Replies: `"Research processing paused. Use !research release to resume."` / `"Research processing resumed."`
- No-ops with a message if already in the requested state

`handleStatusCommand(message)`:
- Reports: hold active/inactive, gate reason (if any), pending item count

`require('./research-gate')` is done **inside** these handlers (lazy) to avoid load-order issues since `discord-bot` is required early in the chain.

